Let me reintroduce myself… My name’s Emily, I’m an Exercise Physiologist and that’s a big part of what’s behind the uplifting, positive energy you see on this page. I actually started on Musical.ly back in the day, just being an uplifting, positive influencer and I genuinely think that energy helped guide me into a career in EP. At my core, I’m driven by values like kindness, growth, authenticity, resilience, and connection and I truly believe that movement, both physical and emotional, has the power to support all of those things. Even the smallest actions can make life feel more meaningful. For a while, I was nervous to share more of this side of my life like my work, my knowledge, my passion because I didn’t feel “qualified enough.” But I’ve come to realise that your story the ups, the uncertainties, and the growth is what truly matters. So here’s to sharing more of my journey and hopefully inspiring you to lean into what feels good for your mind, body, and whole self 💫🤍 #ExercisePhysiology #TikTokIntro #KindnessAndMovement #MentalHealthMatters #GrowthJourney #FeelGoodFitness #MovementIsMedicine #LiveWithHeart #fyp

At this point in my life, I was so obsessed with how I thought my body needed to look. I constantly compared myself to girls I saw on TikTok and Instagram, wondering why my dieting and training didn’t make me look like them. I’ve always struggled with my mental health — and still do — but back then, I tied my worth to how I looked. Since taking this video, I’ve gained weight, and for a long time, I felt ashamed of that. But I’ve also grown in so many ways. I’ve learned to care for my body, not punish it. To move, eat, and rest with love, not guilt. And most importantly, I’ve started to put my mental health first. It’s heartbreaking how much pressure women feel to look a certain way. But our bodies do so much for us — and they deserve respect at every stage. I’m still on this journey of self-love, but I’m in a much healthier, more positive place now. I’m surrounded by people who love me for who I am — not what I look like. Family, friends, and a partner who remind me daily that I’m enough. I’m so grateful for how far I’ve come, and even more grateful for the growth still to come. If you’re struggling, you’re not alone. Be kind to your body, and even kinder to your mind. 🤍 #SelfLoveJourney #MentalHealthAwareness #BodyAcceptance #ProgressNotPerfection #GratefulHeart

When I first moved from Japan to New York City, I was terrified. I didn’t know anyone, didn’t fully know the language, and had no idea what the future would look like. All I had was a suitcase, a dream, and a heart full of uncertainty. I cried in secret, doubted myself often, and questioned whether I belonged. But somehow, step by shaky step, I built a life — a home — in this city that once felt so intimidating. Now, I’m moving again. But this time, it’s different. I’m not alone. I have my family with me, and instead of fear, I feel excitement. Instead of wondering if I’ll survive, I know I’ll thrive. Because I’ve done it before — and I’ve grown into a woman who knows her strength. To any woman out there standing on the edge of the unknown: it’s okay to be scared. But don’t let that fear stop you. You are capable of creating magic in places that feel unfamiliar. Trust yourself. You’ve got this🫶🏻 #lifeupdate #storytime #movingtoaustin #newmomlife #newparent

what you're not changing, you're choosing 🧍🏻‍♀️ Sometimes, we don't feel empowered enough or confident enough to step into our next season. Sometimes we already feel so overwhelmed by the day-to-day that we don't even consider how we could move forward. But if you could take 10 minutes today to sit down and ask yourself, what things you are choosing, that consistently hold you back, it could be a life changer. You might also recognize some hard things that you ARE choosing, because you see how they DO benefit you (or how they might in the future) and that alone can be so empowering. It could be a reminder that although things are tough right now, you know where you are headed and that's worth it. You have so much more control than you think you have. Don't ask yourself what other people want from you. Don't ask yourself what's going to make you look good. Ask yourself what hard things in your life YOU want to choose because this is YOUR life! 🤍 #advice #adviceforwomen #selfgrowth #selfgrowthjourney #mindset #mindsetmatters
